i.e. 'culture', 'discourse', 'identity', 'ideology', 'knowledge', 'LPP', 'multi-competence', and 'power & conflict'. Against this background, this study argues for reconceptualising European multilingualism on the basis of an integrative and multi-focal approach.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLanguage policyxEurope. 0aLanguage policyzEurope. 0aLinguistic minoritiesxEurope. 0aLinguistic minoritieszEurope. 0aMultilingualismxEurope. 0aMultilingualismzEurope. 0aSecond language acquisitionxEurope. 0aSecond language acquisitionzEurope. 0aSecond language acquisition. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh1 aSchjerve, Rosita Rindler, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVetter, Eva, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVetter, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769736340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847697363423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847697363/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK